ensive.\n   - **Unit tests**: `im.service.spec.ts` covers the core functionality
.\n   - **Widget tests**: `im_bloc_test.dart` covers the BLoC.\n   - **Golden te
sts**: Present for design system components.\n\n6. **Documentation Issues**:\n  
- **docs/api/im.md**: Updated with API docs.\n   - **docs/api/socket-events.md**
: Updated with IM events.\n   - **docs/api/INDEX.md**: Updated.\n   - **docs/api
-contracts/im.yaml**: Present.\n\n7. **Potential Blocking Issues**:\n   - **DTO 
type mismatch**: `SendMessageDto.content` is typed as optional (`content?: strin
g`) but has unconditional `@IsString()` validator. This means if `content` is mi
ssing, validation will fail. However, for both text and image messages, content 
is required. The service layer also validates this. But the type definition shou
ld be `content!: string` to match the validation.\n   - **Missing `@IsOptional()
` on content in SendMessageDto**: Actually, looking at the DTO again:\n     ```t
ypescript\n     @IsString()\n     @ValidateIf((o) => o.type === "text")\n     @M
axLength(500)\n     content?: string;\n     ```\n     The `@IsString()` is NOT i
